    "client_msg_id": "33fe58cc-1821-4e06-87db-e4978700815b",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "So far as I know the Greek word for a shape (like a cutout or silhouette) was pulled into philosophy in the late 1700s, after which -&gt; maths/logic -&gt; computer science. Most of the vocabulary of CS was imported by analogy from other disciplines by people who pre-dated the field of CS itself.",
